[~sjones], you were right about changing the cloud property {{objectstorage.max_buckets_per_account}}.  It was set to the default.  I changed it to 3000. 
{code}
[root@a-34-l ~]# euctl objectstorage.max_buckets_per_account
objectstorage.max_buckets_per_account = 3000
{code}
This time, I was able to create 997 stacks:
{code}
[root@a-34-l ~]# euform-describe-stacks --region eng-admin@ | grep STACK | grep BucketStack | awk '{print $3}' | sort | uniq -c
    997 CREATE_COMPLETE
   1003 ROLLBACK_COMPLETE
{code}
I attached the template {{cfn-bucket-nodeletepolicy-template.json}} that was used to create the 2000 stacks.  To create the stacks, I ran the following command:
{code}
[root@a-34-l ~]# for x in {1..2000}; do euform-create-stack BucketStack${x} --template-file cfn-bucket-nodeletepolicy-template.json --region eng-admin@; sleep 1; done
{code}
Let me know if you need any additional information.

*Eucalyptus Version*

{{4.4.0-0.25812.163.20170303gitb711a30.el7}}

*Setup*

# Deployed Eucalyptus VPC, multi-cluster, multi-UFS cloud - [hspencer-529-maint-4.4|http://jenkins.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/job/Quick%20Launch%20Maint_4.4/529/]
# Create non-eucalyptus account (example {{development-operations}}) via {{euare-accountcreate}}
# Set cloud property {{objectstorage.max_buckets_per_account}} to 3000:
{code}
[root@a-34-l ~]# euctl objectstorage.max_buckets_per_account
objectstorage.max_buckets_per_account = 3000
{code}
# Make sure Ceph backend bucket limit matches cloud property {{objectstorage.max_buckets_per_account}} value:
{code}
[root@e-13 ~]# radosgw-admin user modify --uid=hspencer-529-maint-4-4 --max-buckets=3000
